Package com.company.restaurantessentials

Class Order

java.lang.Object
com.company.restaurantessentials.Order
public class Order extends Object
This class is the main entity that processes the Reservation/Orders made by Customers. This class has the following attributes:
  1. Customer object
  2. orderNumber
  3. groupSize
  4. tableNumber
  5. date
  6. reservationStartTime
  7. reservationEndTime
  8. reservationIsActive (boolean value)
  9. Staff object
  10. Map of MenuItem as Key and Quantity as value (i.e Laksa,2)
  11. Map of PromotionPackage as Key and Quantity as value
  12. orderIsActive (boolean value)

This class has 2 main function:

  1. Reservation
    • Upon Successful reservation, a new Order object is created with an 'active reservation' and 'inactive order'.
  2. Ordering
    • When the Customer successfully checks-in, the order becomes 'active' and the relevant MenuItems and PromotionPackages can then be added accordingly.

    • editQuantity

      public void editQuantity(MenuItem item, int newQuantity)
      This functions allows the staff to edit the item that is already added to the order. The new quantity will override the current quantity. (i.e. if the initial Quantity for Ice Cream was '4', and '2' was passed in to this function, then the quantity will be updated to 2
      Parameters:
      item - the MenuItem object that needs to be edited
      newQuantity - the new quantity required.
